The paper is about convolutional networks for object recognition tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the vanishing-gradient problem and parameter efficiency, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG and cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture for convolutional networks, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or natural language processing (cs.CL) if the architecture is applied to text data.
